{#def preset, selected=False, extra="" #}
{#
  Selectable "where to run" card for the create page -- the two compute
  presets (Imbue Cloud / local) compose from this. Renders a
  ``<button type="button">`` with ``role="radio"``; selection is driven by
  ``aria-checked`` (the create page's inline JS flips it), exactly like the
  ColorSwatch picker. The visual state is pure Tailwind:

    - default: a 2px dashed neutral border (``border-dashed border-strong``);
    - selected: a solid accent border + a faint accent tint, via the
      ``aria-checked:`` variants (so the JS only toggles the attribute, no
      class bookkeeping);
    - hover: lifts with ``shadow-raised`` -- the interactive-card hover from
      the styleguide -- rather than a heavier border.

  The border width is a constant 2px across states (only its style/color
  changes) so selecting never shifts layout. The caller supplies the title /
  badge / feature list as the component body.

  Props:
    preset    the ``data-preset`` value (``"remote"`` / ``"local"``); the
              page JS reads it to apply that preset's provider defaults.
    selected  initial ``aria-checked`` state (one card per radiogroup).
    extra     parent-owned sizing (e.g. ``flex-1``); the component root
              carries no outer positioning of its own.

  Any other HTML attribute (id=, data-*, aria-label=) flows through via
  JinjaX's ``attrs`` passthrough.
#}
{%- set _base = "flex flex-col gap-2 p-4 text-left cursor-pointer rounded-lg bg-surface-primary border-2 border-dashed border-strong hover:shadow-raised aria-checked:border-solid aria-checked:border-accent aria-checked:bg-accent/5" -%}
<button {{ attrs.render(
  type="button",
  role="radio",
  classes=_base ~ " " ~ extra,
  **{"data-preset": preset, "aria-checked": "true" if selected else "false"},
) }}>{{ content }}</button>
